lead_paragraph: Former U.S. Secretary of State Hillary Clinton remained vague on Monday about whether she would run for president in 2016 and said the militant attack in Benghazi, Libya, was the biggest regret of her four years as the top U.S. diplomat.

headline.main: Hillary Clinton Mum on Presidency, Says Benghazi Her Biggest Regret
